tates%20District%20Court%20for%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%2C%20an%20appointee%20of%20former%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush%2C%20said%20the%20executive%20order%20against%20WilmerHale%20was%20a%20form%20of%20%26quot%3Bcoercion%26quot%3B%20against%20the%20firm%20to%20%26quot%3Bsuppress%20WilmerHale's%20representation%20of%20disfavored%20causes%20and%20clients.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20concluded%20that%20this%20Order%20must%20be%20struck%20down%20in%20its%20entirety%20as%20unconstitutional%2C%26quot%3B%20Leon%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIndeed%2C%20to%20rule%20otherwise%20would%20be%20unfaithful%20to%20the%20judgment%20and%20vision%20of%20the%20Founding%20Fathers!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20marks%20the%20third%20straight%20victory%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-big-law-fight-firms-legal-dilemma-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elaw%20firms%20suing%20the%20Trump%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20executive%20orders%20targeting%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudges%20have%20also%20blocked%20executive%20orders%20targeting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-blocks-donald-trump-executive-order-big-law-perkins-coie-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPerkins%20Coie%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-executive-order-targeting-jenner-block-big-law-unconstitutional-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJenner%20%26amp%3B%20Block%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20final%20decision%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-big-law-executive-orders-decisions-damage-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESusman%20Godfrey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20fourth%20and%20most%20recent%20firm%20to%20sue%20the%20administration%2C%20remains%20pending%2C%20although%20a%20judge%20has%20already%20placed%20a%20restraining%20order%20preventing%20the%20implementation%20of%20Trump's%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20May%2C%20WilmerHale's%20attorneys%20said%20the%20Trump%20administration%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwilmerhale-lawyers-security-clearances-trump-executive-orders-big-law-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuspended%20the%20security%20clearances%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20two%20of%20its%20lawyers.%20Judge%20Leon's%20order%20on%20Tuesday%20requires%20government%20agencies%20to%20%26quot%3Bimmediately%20take%20any%20and%20all%20steps%20necessary%20to%20nullify%20and%20reverse%20any%20implementation%26quot%3B%20of%20Trump's%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Court's%20decision%20to%20permanently%20block%20the%20unlawful%20executive%20order%20in%20its%20entirety%20strongly%20affirms%20our%20foundational%20constitutional%20rights%20and%20those%20of%20our%20clients%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20WilmerHale%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20remain%20proud%20to%20defend%20our%20firm%2C%20our%20people%2C%20and%20our%20clients.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarrison%20Fields%2C%20principal%20deputy%20press%20secretary%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20White%20House%20opposes%20Judge%20Leon's%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20decision%20to%20grant%20any%20individual%20access%20to%20this%20nation's%20secrets%20is%20a%20sensitive%20judgment%20call%20entrusted%20to%20the%20President%2C%26quot%3B%20Fields%20said.%20%26quot%3BWeighing%20these%20factors%20and%20implementing%20such%20decisions%20are%20core%20executive%20powers%2C%20and%20reviewing%20the%20President's%20clearance%20decisions%20falls%20well%20outside%20the%20judiciary's%20authority.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20can%20appeal%20Judge%20Leon's%20decision%2C%20in%20which%20case%20the%20proceedings%20will%20be%20heard%20in%20the%20court%20of%20appeals.%20Any%20subsequent%20appeal%20would%20be%20heard%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFields%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider%20when%20asked%20if%20the%20government%20would%20appeal%20Judge%20Leon's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20now-blocked%20executive%20order%2C%20Trump%20specifically%20singled%20out%20attorney%20Aaron%20Zebley%2C%20a%20WilmerHale%20employee%20who%20served%20as%20a%20top%20aide%20in%20Robert%20Mueller's%20special%20counsel's%20office%2C%20which%20investigated%20Trump's%20ties%20to%20Russia%20in%202016.%20The%20order%20described%20WilmerHale's%20decision%20to%20hire%20Zebley%20after%20his%20participation%20in%20the%20federal%20probe%20as%20%26quot%3Bweaponization%20of%20the%20justice%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilmerHale%20hired%20the%20superstar%20conservative%20lawyer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwilmerhale-jenner-fight-trump-executive-order-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPaul%20Clement%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20defend%20the%20firm%20in%20its%20suit%20against%20the%20Trump%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20ruling%2C%20Judge%20Leon%20wrote%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bobvious%26quot%3B%20that%20enforcing%20Trump's%20order%20against%20WilmerHale%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bcontrary%20to%20the%20public%20interest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20WilmerHale%20Order%20violates%20the%20separation%20of%20powers%20by%20attempting%20to%20usurp%20the%20Judiciary's%20authority%20to%20resolve%20cases%20and%20sanction%20abuses%20of%20the%20judicial%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Jude%20Leon%20wrote.%20%26quot%3B'A%20scheme%20so%20inconsistent%20with%20accepted%20separation-of-powers%20principles'%20must%20fall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-executive-order-wilmerhale-big-law-unconstitutional-coercion-retaliat