0staff.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERead%20the%20memos%20from%20the%20Post's%20executive%20editor%2C%20Matt%20Murray%2C%20and%20deputy%20opinion%20editor%20Mary%20Duenwald.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20is%20offering%20buyouts%20to%20select%20teams%20as%20part%20of%20a%20restructuring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLike%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20industry%2C%20we%20are%20adapting%20to%20changing%20habits%20and%20new%20technologies%2C%26quot%3B%20its%20executive%20editor%2C%20Matt%20Murray%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20memo%20to%20staff%20sent%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BTo%20reach%20new%20audiences%20we%20must%20increase%20our%20staffing%20flexibility%20and%20expand%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20audience%20data%20and%20social%20video.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20voluntary%20buyouts%20are%20set%20to%20be%20offered%20to%20news%20employees%20with%20a%20tenure%20of%20at%20least%2010%20years%20at%20the%20Post%2C%20as%20well%20as%20all%20members%20of%20the%20video%20department%2C%20copy%20desks%2C%20and%20opinion%20section.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20period%20to%20accept%20the%20buyouts%20is%20scheduled%20to%20last%20roughly%20two%20months%2C%20ending%20in%20July.%20The%20announcement%20comes%20as%20Post%20employees%20are%20set%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereturn%20to%20a%20five-day%20in-office%20workweek%20next%20week%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20memo%2C%20Murray%20outlined%20changes%20to%20the%20video%20and%20copy%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20video%2C%20he%20said%20the%20company%20would%20focus%20more%20on%20%26quot%3Brepeatable%20franchises%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpersonality-driven%20formats%20for%20YouTube%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20embedding%20producers%20within%20the%20newsroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20also%20plans%20to%20restructure%20its%20copy%20teams%20to%20combine%20all%20editing%20operations%20into%20one%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20memo%2C%20the%20deputy%20opinion%20editor%20Mary%20Duenwald%20wrote%20that%20the%20opinion%20section%20was%20still%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20top%20editor%20and%20would%20soon%20%26quot%3Bcarry%20out%20in%20earnest%26quot%3B%20a%20plan%20announced%20in%20February%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-wapo-columnists-must-defend-free-markets-personal-liberties-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efocus%20on%20personal%20liberties%20and%20free%20markets%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIdeally%2C%20our%20new%20editor%20will%20be%20known%20before%20the%20time%20is%20up%26quot%3B%20to%20decide%20on%20taking%20a%20buyout%2C%20Duenwald%20wrote.%20She%20said%20the%20offer%20was%20%26quot%3Bmeant%20to%20give%20people%20security%20to%20make%20a%20clear-eyed%20decision%20on%20whether%20they%20want%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20new%20direction%20for%20Post%20Opinion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Jeff%20Bezos-owned%20newspaper%20sparked%20a%20backlash%20last%20year%20after%20opting%20not%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-washington-post-subscriptions-cancel-president-endorse-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eendorse%20a%20candidate%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20presidential%20election%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwashington-post-staff-revolt-presidential-endorsement-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirst%20time%20in%2040%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20more%20than%20400%20staffers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-washington-post-staffers-petition-to-bezos-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eurged%20Bezos%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20meet%20with%20company%20leaders%2C%20saying%20that%20integrity%20and%20transparency%20issues%20had%20sparked%20high-level%20departures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Bezos%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-wapo-columnists-must-defend-free-markets-personal-liberties-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoverhauled%20the%20opinion%20section%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20announced%20David%20Shipley%2C%20the%20section's%20editor%2C%20would%20be%20stepping%20down.%20In%20March%2C%20Murray%20detailed%20further%20organizational%20changes%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaked-wapo-memo-reveals-big-changes-coming-to-bezos-newsroom-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enew%20leadership%20roles%20and%20reorganized%20teams%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Post%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20had%20been%20going%20through%20a%20serious%20and%20significant%20transformation%20in%20recent%20months%20and%20called%20the%20voluntary%20buyouts%20an%20inflection%20point%20for%20employees%20to%20ask%20themselves%20whether%20they%20want%20to%20stay%20or%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Washington%20Post%20is%20continuing%20its%20transformation%20to%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20industry%2C%20build%20a%20more%20sustainable%20future%20and%20reach%20audiences%20where%20they%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20Murray's%20memo%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EDear%20All%2C%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EToday%2C%20we%20are%20announcing%20that%20The%20Washington%20Post%20is%20offering%20a%20Voluntary%20Separation%20Program%20(VSP)%20to%20news%20employees%20with%2010%20or%20more%20years'%20service%20at%20The%20Post%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20all%20members%20of%20the%20video%20department%20and%20to%20all%20members%20of%20the%20copy%20desk%20and%20sports%20copy%20desk.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20program%20is%20part%20of%20our%20ongoing%20newsroom%20transformation%20efforts%20aimed%20at%20reshaping%20and%20modernizing%20the%20newsroom%20for%20the%20current%20environment.%20Like%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20industry%2C%20we%20are%20adapting%20to%20changing%20habits%20and%20new%20technologies%20that%20are%20transforming%20news%20experiences.%20Even%20as%20we%20have%20begun%20creating%20new%20departments%20and%20welcoming%20new%20colleagues%2C%20to%20reach%20new%20audiences%20we%20must%20increase%20our%20staffing%20flexibility%20and%20expand%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20audience%20data%20and%20social%20video.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EOur%20efforts%20are%20beginning%20to%20bear%20fruit.%20We%20are%20producing%20a%20more%20diverse%20news%20report%20with%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20superb%20and%20impactful%20journalism.%20I%20am%20confident%20we%20have%20exciting%20opportunities%20ahead%20of%20us.%20I%20also%20recognize%2C%20as%20I%20said%20at%20the%20all-staff%20meeting%20in%20March%2C%20that%20reimagining%20the%20newsroom%2C%20rethinking%20all%20we%20do%20and%20how%20we%20do%20it%2C%20is%20disruptive%20and%20even%20uncomfortable.%20The%20VSP%20presents%20an%20opportunity%20to%20colleagues%20who%20may%20want%20to%20pursue%20alternatives.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EIn%20that%20light%20the%20VSP%20is%20being%20offered%20to%20the%20entirety%20of%20the%20video%20team%20and%20to%20the%20copy%20desks.%20In%20the%20former%20case%2C%20we%20are%20restructuring%20and%20refocusing%20our%20video%20team%20to%20place%20much%20greater%20emphasis%20on%20developing%20repeatable%20franchises%20and%20more%20personality-driven%20formats%20for%20YouTube%2C%20other%20social%20media%20channels%20and%20off-platform%20more%20broadly%2C%20while%20embedding%20some%20video%20producers%20and%20facilitators%20in%20the%20core%20newsroom%20to%20help%20all%20our%20journalists%20and%20artists%20produce%20more%20video%20for%20our%20products.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EOn%20the%20editing%20front%2C%20we%20aim%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20to%20combine%20operations%20to%20one%20desk%20that%20will%20be%20part%20of%20the%20central%20news%20hub%20and%20ultimately%20will%20serve%20our%20digital%20products%20full%20time.%20The%20new%20print%20desk%20will%20also%20have%20a%20handful%20of%20crucial%20editing%20roles.%20These%20changes%20will%20enhance%20the%20speed%20and%20quality%20of%20our%20digital%20products%20and%20free%20most%20of%20us%20from%20constraints%20imposed%20by%20print%20requirements%E2%80%94while%20preserving%20the%20editing%20standards%20that%20undergird%20our%20focus%20on%20accuracy%2C%20clarity%20and%20credibility.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EI%20want%20to%20underscore%20that%20the%20VSP%20is%20voluntary%2C%20and%20that%20we%20are%20fortunate%20we%20can%20offer%20enhanced%20packages%20for%20those%20who%20choose%20them.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EToday's%20announcement%20kicks%20off%20an%20approximately%20two-month%20process%20that%20should%20culminate%20around%20the%20end%20of%20July.%20Eligible%20employees%20will%20receive%20a%20note%20with%20more%20details%20of%20the%20VSP%20later%20this%20morning%20from%20Wayne%20Connell.%20We%20will%20meet%20with%20the%20video%20team%20and%20editing%20desks%20later%20today%20and%20hold%20an%20information%20session%20for%20all%20others%20who%20are%20eligible.%20We%20also%20will%20schedule%20training%20and%20information%20sessions%20for%20managers%20in%20coming%20days.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EIn%20coming%20weeks%2C%20we%20will%20name%20a%20print%20editor%20and%20welcome%20Jason%20Anders%2C%20the%20new%20ME%20for%20the%20news%20hub%2C%20and%20with%20them%20share%20more%20detailed%20plans%20on%20the%20new%20editing%20desks.%20And%20I%20expect%20to%20hold%20another%20all-staff%20in%20June%20to%20update%20everyone%20on%20our%20progress.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20please%20feel%20free%20to%20bring%20your%20questions%20to%20Wayne%20and%20Liz%20Seymour.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EWith%20the%20VSP%2C%20we%20will%20no%20doubt%20see%20valued%20colleagues%20and%20friends%20decide%20to%20leave%20The%20Post.%20But%20as%20stewards%20of%20this%20great%20institution%2C%20we%20all%20must%20remain%20relentlessly%20focused%20on%20bringing%20engaging%20and%20relevant%20journalism%20to%20growing%20numbers%20of%20readers%20in%20the%20formats%20and%20ways%20they%20want%20it%20in%202025.%20That%20is%20an%20urgent%20and%20important%20task%20for%20us%20given%20the%20pace%20of%20technological%20change%2C%20the%20industry's%20evolving%20landscape%20and%20the%20ever-present%20need%20to%20produce%20and%20promote%20strong%2C%20rigorous%20and%20independent%20journalism.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EMatt%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20Duenwald's%20memo%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EDear%20Dept%20of%20Opinions%2C%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EIt's%20been%20a%20few%20months%20since%20we%20learned%20about%20changes%20ahead%20for%20Post%20Opinion.%20We're%20closer%20to%20the%20time%20when%20the%20section%20will%20begin%20to%20carry%20out%20in%20earnest%20the%20plan%20laid%20out%20in%20February%20to%20devote%20attention%20to%20personal%20liberties%20and%20free%20markets.%20So%20it's%20important%20to%20begin%20to%20transition%20to%20this%20time%20of%20reimagining%20Post%20Opinion.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EToday%2C%20the%20company%20is%20announcing%20a%20voluntary%20separation%20program%20for%20Opinion.%20All%20eligible%20employees%20in%20our%20section%20will%20receive%20an%20email%20from%20Wayne%20Connell%20shortly%20laying%20out%20the%20details%20(contractors%20and%20freelancers%20will%20not).%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EPlease%20know%20that%20all%20of%20us%20will%20have%20time%20to%20make%20up%20our%20minds%20about%20whether%20to%20accept%20this%20offer.%20The%20decision%20period%20will%20run%20until%20the%20end%20of%20July.%20Ideally%2C%20our%20new%20editor%20will%20be%20known%20before%20the%20time%20is%20up.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThis%20voluntary%20offer%20is%20meant%20to%20give%20people%20security%20to%20make%20a%20clear-eyed%20decision%20on%20whether%20they%20want%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20new%20direction%20for%20Post%20Opinion.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EI'm%20happy%20to%20discuss%20this%2C%20of%20course.%20At%2011%3A30%2