mething%20that%20isn%E2%80%99t%20really%20there.%20Delusions%20are%20fixed%20false%20beliefs%2C%20like%20thinking%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20harm%20you%2C%20or%20that%20you%20have%20extraordinary%20powers%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr.%20Khanna%20explained.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20symptoms%20are%20different%20for%20each%20person%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20someone%20dangerous.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F136309%2Fmental-health-stigma-taboos-depression%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindividuals%20with%20schizophrenia%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20vulnerable%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20harm%20than%20to%20cause%20it.%20Many%20live%20with%20fear%2C%20confusion%2C%20or%20distress%2C%20not%20aggression.%20The%20assumption%20that%20someone%20with%20schizophrenia%20is%20unsafe%20often%20leads%20to%20isolation%20and%20shame%2C%20making%20recovery%20even%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMyth%203%3A%20%E2%80%9CThey%20can%E2%80%99t%20live%20normal%20lives%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20diagnosis%20of%20schizophrenia%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20life%20stops.%20With%20access%20to%20the%20right%20care%2C%20many%20people%20continue%20to%20work%2C%20build%20relationships%2C%20raise%20families%2C%20and%20live%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20entirely%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr.%20Khanna.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20key%20is%20consistent%20treatment%2C%20which%20includes%20regular%20medication%2C%20therapy%2C%20and%20strong%20support%20from%20family%20or%20caregivers.%E2%80%9D%20She%20emphasises%20that%20schizophrenia%20requires%20ongoing%20care%2C%20and%20stopping%20treatment%20abruptly%20can%20lead%20to%20relapses.%20But%20stability%20and%20fulfilment%20are%20very%20much%20within%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20people%20return%20to%20jobs%2C%20reconnect%20with%20loved%20ones%2C%20an